rComments: Great Professor, group projects were easy and tutorials were great. No textbook required
Great prof. Easy and understandable. Readings were basic, material was interesting.

He is a good professor but his courses involve a lot of participation within groups. You have to attend almost every lecture and every tutorial session. In addition to small group activities, there is a time consuming group project during the second half of the course that you and your group members have to do on your own time.

He is a really nice person and gives interesting lectures. He is a big believer in group work, which actually does help in understanding the material. Based on student feedback he now makes the marks individual, so you don't have to worry about lazy group members affecting your mark. Do the work and participate and the course will be a breeze.

One of the best profs I've ever had. Interesting lectures; you can tell he loves teaching and is passionate about what he's talking about. Super straight-forward assignments and exams that allow you to show what you know and what you've learned, and his marking is fair. He talks to you like a person, not a student.

Amazing prof. He scanned the textbook so we didn't have to buy it, which was so nice! Lectures are great and they work well with the readings. I learned a lot from him. Heavy on participation - every week there's group work in the lecture. The group work is super easy and relevant (helps with midterm, assignments, etc).
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Amazing professor. Very engaging and enthusiastic about the material.  fair marker, just do your work and you will get a good grade. Lectures are long but he puts in a few jokes here and there.  you will definitely learn a lot in his course.

AVOID. Participation was GRADED rather than completenot complete. Tough grader makes you work for your grade. Summer course was brutal. He had a final exam, saved 60% of the course due in the last week of school. SO MUCH GROUP WORK. Very short and lacking lectures but makes you stay till the end. Not inspirational. Waste of my money and time.
